## Design rationale

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **Boundary values** | Parametrised tests hit `1`, `30`, `31` explicitly as required by the spec transition points. |
| **HR-approval routing** | Tests assert both the flag on the returned object *and* that the approval router is called once (and only once). |
| **Employee type guard** | Separate class with positive (full-time) and negative (part-time, contractor) cases; verifies side-effect-free failure. |
| **Idempotency** | Repository mock is pre-loaded with the cached result on the second call; tests verify `save()` and `route_to_hr_admin()` are each called at most once regardless of retry count. |
| **Idempotency-before-validation** | One test specifically confirms the cache lookup short-circuits all downstream validation, which is the safe pattern for retry logic. |
| **Isolation** | All external collaborators (repository, approval router) are `MagicMock`s; no real I/O or databases involved. |
